[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The key principle: never let a transient infrastructure failure block claim processing. The primary XGBoost model (Recipe 7.11) can always produce a score independently. The similarity layer adds confidence and explanation; when it's unavailable, you lose those signals but claims still flow. The SQS dead-letter queue captures claims that fail all retries so nothing is silently dropped.
